02:46.253 --> 02:47.428
-HE STINKS OF ALCOHOL.

02:49.691 --> 02:51.954
WELL, LET'S WAKE HIM UP.

02:52.084 --> 02:53.651
-BE CAREFUL.

02:53.782 --> 02:55.697
MOST OF THESE GUYS ARE
HARMLESS, BUT YOU NEVER KNOW.

02:55.827 --> 02:58.526
-HEY, BUDDY. COME
ON, TIME TO WAKE UP.

02:58.656 --> 03:00.354
-[MAN GROANS]

03:02.312 --> 03:03.835
-OH MY GOD.

03:05.924 --> 03:07.143
IT'S JOHN.

03:07.665 --> 03:08.840
-CORT.

03:08.971 --> 03:11.103
-JOHN, IT'S ME. IT'S C.J.

03:13.018 --> 03:14.237
-[GASPS]

03:15.238 --> 03:16.370
C.J.

03:18.894 --> 03:20.069
HEY, SWEET THING.

03:21.462 --> 03:22.463
HOW YOU DOIN'?

03:24.073 --> 03:25.727
HEY, GIVE ME A LITTLE KISS, HUH?

03:25.857 --> 03:26.989
-JOHN, DON'T.

03:27.119 --> 03:28.773
-COME ON, COME ON.

03:28.904 --> 03:30.210
-COME ON, YOU'RE DRUNK.

03:30.340 --> 03:31.298
YOU'RE EMBARRASSING YOURSELF.

03:31.428 --> 03:32.864
MATT'S HERE.

03:33.909 --> 03:34.997
-WELL, HE'S NOT HERE FOR ME

03:35.127 --> 03:36.825
'CAUSE I CAN'T SEE HIM.

03:38.130 --> 03:39.654
I ONLY HAVE EYES FOR YOU, DEAR.

03:39.784 --> 03:41.482
-KNOCK IT OFF, CORT.

03:41.612 --> 03:43.310
-[GRUNTS] OR WHAT?

03:44.615 --> 03:45.747
COME ON!

03:47.139 --> 03:48.837
TAKE YOUR BEST SHOT, HUH.

03:48.967 --> 03:50.317
I'LL BREAK YOU IN HALF.

03:50.447 --> 03:52.014
[GRUNTS]

03:52.144 --> 03:55.104
-OH GOD. [MUMBLED SPEECH]

03:56.018 --> 03:57.846
-COULD YOU FIND HIM
SOME CLOTHES, PLEASE?

03:57.976 --> 03:59.848
-[GRUNTING] OH, I LOOK
BEST IN ROYAL BLUE.

03:59.978 --> 04:01.719
-WHY DON'T YOU
FIND SOME CLOTHES?

04:01.850 --> 04:03.460
I DON'T FEEL COMFORTABLE WITH
YOU TAKIN' OFF HIS CLOTHES.

04:03.591 --> 04:05.288
-OH, GUYS.

04:05.419 --> 04:06.985
-ARE YOU KIDDING? THIS IS
HARDLY A ROMANTIC SITUATION.

04:07.116 --> 04:09.074
-OH, C.J., IT'S VERY ROMANTIC.

04:09.205 --> 04:11.729
-HE NEEDS US. I CAN'T TURN
MY BACK ON HIM RIGHT NOW.

04:11.860 --> 04:14.036
-OH. TERRIBLE!

04:14.166 --> 04:15.472
-SHUT UP!

04:15.603 --> 04:16.952
-DON'T WORRY. I'M
IN LOVE WITH YOU.

04:17.082 --> 04:18.692
I'M NOT IN LOVE WITH CORT, OKAY?

04:18.822 --> 04:20.084
-OH, COME ON, C.J.
-IT'S NOT AN ISSUE.

04:20.216 --> 04:22.043
-YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH ME.
-CUT IT OUT!

04:22.174 --> 04:24.568
-[GROANS]

04:24.699 --> 04:27.658
AH. C.J.

04:29.312 --> 04:32.097
-[PHONE RINGING IN BACKGROUND]

04:34.186 --> 04:37.973
-[PEOPLE CHATTING IN BACKGROUND]

04:42.499 --> 04:44.284
-THIS IS ABOUT YOUR
EYESIGHT, ISN'T IT?

04:46.634 --> 04:48.244
HOW BAD HAS IT GOTTEN?

04:49.245 --> 04:50.812
-WELL, IT'S REALLY
NOT A PROBLEM.

04:52.683 --> 04:55.033
I'M LOOKING FORWARD TO MY
NEW CAREER SELLING PENCILS.

04:55.904 --> 04:57.427
-YOU DON'T HAVE TO
BE SARCASTIC, JOHN.

04:57.558 --> 04:58.776
I'M JUST TRYIN' TO HELP YOU.

04:59.386 --> 05:00.604
-THEN THROW ME A PARTY.

05:01.736 --> 05:03.694
YOU CAN ALL HANG OUT
AND WATCH ME GO BLIND.

05:03.825 --> 05:05.522
I'LL TELL YA WHEN THE
LIGHTS HAVE GONE OUT

05:05.653 --> 05:07.524
SO YOU KNOW WHEN TO
POP THE CHAMPAGNE.

05:07.655 --> 05:09.047
-IT SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

05:09.178 --> 05:10.614
-OH, YOU DON'T
WANNA HELP ME, C.J.

05:11.615 --> 05:13.138
I'LL ONLY BRING YOU DOWN.

05:13.269 --> 05:14.923
EVERYTHING I TOUCH
TURNS TO CRAP.

05:15.880 --> 05:17.142
[SIGHS]

05:19.188 --> 05:20.624
JUST STAY AWAY FROM ME.

05:20.755 --> 05:22.409
-I CAN'T.

05:23.061 --> 05:26.064
I CAN'T STAND BACK AND WATCH
SOMEONE I REALLY CARE ABOUT

05:26.195 --> 05:27.457
SELF DESTRUCT.

05:33.333 --> 05:35.117
WHY AREN'T YOU WEARING THESE?

05:37.728 --> 05:39.121
-[GLASSES CLATTER]

05:39.251 --> 05:41.079
-TO HELL WITH THEM.
I'D RATHER GO BLIND.

05:42.037 --> 05:43.386
[SIGHS]

05:45.257 --> 05:46.737
-WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

05:51.263 --> 05:53.396
-[WAVES CRASHING]

05:55.703 --> 05:57.835
-ALL RIGHT, HOBE-STER!

06:00.969 --> 06:02.013
-HEY!

06:04.929 --> 06:06.148
-WELL, YOU'RE THE
ONLY GUY I KNOW

06:06.278 --> 06:08.542
WHO COMES TO WORK
ON HIS DAY OFF.

06:08.672 --> 06:11.458
-WHAT A BEAUTIFUL
GIRL. [CHUCKLES]

06:11.588 --> 06:14.025
HOW CAN YOU STAY AWAY FROM
THE BEACH ON A DAY LIKE TODAY?

06:14.156 --> 06:15.418
-MITCH, I'D LIKE
TO INTRODUCE YOU

06:15.549 --> 06:16.811
TO A VERY GOOD FRIEND OF MINE.

06:16.941 --> 06:18.987
NICHOLAS, THIS IS
MITCH BUCHANNON.

06:19.117 --> 06:20.336
-HEY, NICK. NICE TO MEET YA.

06:21.424 --> 06:22.599
-SAME HERE.

06:22.730 --> 06:24.384
CAN I GO DOWN TO THE WATER NOW?

06:24.514 --> 06:27.212
-OH, SURE. YEAH.
JUST BE CAREFUL.

06:27.996 --> 06:30.346
-STEP INTO MY
OFFICE. [CHUCKLES]

06:40.748 --> 06:42.184
WHAT'S HE GOT?

06:43.359 --> 06:46.449
-LEUKEMIA AND THE
CHEMOTHERAPY'S NOT WORKING.

06:47.363 --> 06:49.409
HE'S GONNA NEED A BONE
MARROW TRANSPLANT.

06:51.106 --> 06:53.413
-WOW. HOW'D YOU GET INVOLVED?

06:54.109 --> 06:57.373
-I DO VOLUNTEER WORK WITH THE
HOSPICE WHERE NICK IS LIVING.

06:58.418 --> 07:01.333
HIS PARENTS DIED ABOUT A
YEAR AGO IN A CAR ACCIDENT

07:02.378 --> 07:03.858
AND HE HAD BEEN LIVING
IN A FOSTER HOME

07:03.988 --> 07:06.730
UP UNTIL HE STARTED HIS
CHEMOTHERAPY TREATMENTS.

07:07.905 --> 07:10.081
THE DOCTOR SAYS HIS
CHANCES ARE PRETTY GOOD

07:10.212 --> 07:12.388
IF THE SURGERY IS SUCCESSFUL.

07:14.259 --> 07:16.087
LOOK AT THE LITTLE GUY.

07:16.697 --> 07:18.655
HE SHOULD BE THINKIN'
ABOUT BASEBALL,

07:18.786 --> 07:21.571
NOT THE LATEST ADVANCEMENT
IN CANCER TREATMENTS.

07:22.224 --> 07:24.748
I DON'T KNOW HOW HE
KEEPS HIS SPIRITS UP.

07:26.968 --> 07:28.404
-YOU KNOW, IF HE
CAN SWIM ALL RIGHT,

07:28.535 --> 07:30.145
HOBIE AND I CAN GET HIM
UP ON A BOOGIE BOARD.

07:30.275 --> 07:32.234
-OH, HE'D BE THRILLED.

07:33.583 --> 07:35.106
-[INDISTINCT TALKING]

07:35.237 --> 07:36.412
-ARE YOU READY?

07:37.500 --> 07:38.501
-OKAY.

07:38.632 --> 07:39.894
-HERE COMES A GOOD ONE. READY?

07:40.024 --> 07:41.199
OKAY, HOLD ON.

07:41.330 --> 07:42.331
ALL RIGHT, HERE IT COMES.

07:42.462 --> 07:44.899
-ALL RIGHT. GO, GO, GO, GO, GO!

07:45.029 --> 07:46.553
-[WATER RUSHING]

07:46.683 --> 07:48.424
-[MITCH CLAPS AND LAUGHS]

07:51.906 --> 07:54.386
-MAN, IT REALLY BUMS ME OUT
WHEN I SEE A KID LIKE NICK.

07:55.083 --> 07:56.606
-IT SHOULD MAKE YOU SAD, PAL.

07:57.520 --> 07:59.566
IT SHOULD ALSO MAKE YOU
REALIZE HOW LUCKY YOU ARE.

07:59.696 --> 08:00.610
-YEAH.

08:00.741 --> 08:02.569
-ALL RIGHT. WOO!

08:03.221 --> 08:05.659
-[INSPIRATIONAL MUSIC]

08:29.987 --> 08:35.950
♪ THANKFUL FOR A SMILE FROM A FRIEND

08:42.390 --> 08:46.526
♪ AMNESIA FOR A WHILE

08:46.656 --> 08:49.529
