11:11.583 --> 11:13.063
-HEY, GUYS!

11:13.194 --> 11:15.022
HAVE FUN. I'M GOIN' IN!

11:15.152 --> 11:17.067
-OKAY.
-HOBIE: COME ON, LET'S GO.

11:20.418 --> 11:21.855
-I THOUGHT YOU SAID
THIS WAS HIS DAY OFF.

11:22.464 --> 11:23.770
-WHY, WHAT'S WRONG?

11:25.249 --> 11:27.034
-I'M NOT READY FOR THIS.

11:36.478 --> 11:39.133
-[EXHALES SHARPLY]

11:40.221 --> 11:41.744
WHAT'S GOIN' ON WITH HIM?

11:42.484 --> 11:45.400
-[SIGHS] I FOUND HIM
UNDER MY TOWER, DRUNK.

11:46.662 --> 11:48.446
HE'S BEEN LIVING ON THE STREET.

11:49.709 --> 11:50.884
HE'S A MESS.

11:52.799 --> 11:54.844
I THINK HIS RP HAS
GOTTEN A LOT WORSE.

11:55.584 --> 11:57.107
SEEMS LIKE HE'S LOST ALL HOPE.

11:58.500 --> 12:00.284
MAYBE YOU CAN GET
THROUGH TO HIM.

12:01.242 --> 12:02.547
I COULDN'T.

12:03.548 --> 12:04.767
-THANKS.

12:06.377 --> 12:08.075
[SIGHS]

12:09.119 --> 12:11.600
-[BEACHGOERS TALKING
IN BACKGROUND]

12:14.603 --> 12:16.387
-[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

12:20.130 --> 12:21.218
-HEY.

12:22.045 --> 12:23.003
-I ALREADY KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE GONNA SAY,

12:23.133 --> 12:24.178
SO DON'T WASTE YOUR BREATH.

12:27.529 --> 12:28.791
-WELL, I WAS WONDERIN'
HOW LONG IT'D TAKE YOU

12:28.922 --> 12:29.923
TO HIT THE SKIDS.

12:31.185 --> 12:32.664
-WHAT, DID YOU GUYS
HAVE A POOL GOING?

12:32.795 --> 12:34.014
-WHY'D YOU COME BACK?

12:34.144 --> 12:35.450
-THOUGHT I HAD
SOME FRIENDS HERE.

12:36.016 --> 12:38.845
-YOU DO. JOHN, I'LL
ALWAYS BE HERE FOR YOU.

12:39.976 --> 12:41.673
I'LL OFFER YOU
ANYTHING YOU WANT.

12:41.804 --> 12:45.329
FOOD, MONEY, PLACE
TO STAY, YOU NAME IT.

12:46.809 --> 12:48.550
-I DON'T WANT
ANYTHING FROM YOU.

12:48.680 --> 12:50.073
-EXCEPT PITY.

12:51.074 --> 12:52.380
HEY, DON'T GET ME WRONG, PAL.

12:52.510 --> 12:53.903
YOU DESERVE YOUR FAIR SHARE.

12:55.339 --> 12:57.254
BELIEVE ME, I WOULDN'T
WANNA BE IN YOUR SHOES.

13:00.910 --> 13:03.173
BUT YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY
ONE WHO CAUGHT A BAD BREAK

13:03.304 --> 13:04.653
IN THIS WORLD.

13:07.090 --> 13:08.918
SEE THAT LITTLE GUY OUT
THERE SURFIN' WITH HOBIE?

13:12.574 --> 13:13.793
HE'S 10 YEARS OLD.

13:15.316 --> 13:17.448
HE'LL NEED A MIRACLE
TO MAKE IT TO 11.

13:19.537 --> 13:20.756
-WHY?

13:22.540 --> 13:24.281
-HE'S DYING OF LEUKEMIA.

13:24.412 --> 13:27.458
-[SORROWFUL MUSIC]

13:28.503 --> 13:30.287
-JOHN, HE IS DYING.

13:31.985 --> 13:34.552
KINDA PUTS THINGS IN
PERSPECTIVE, DOESN'T IT?

13:36.119 --> 13:38.469
-YEAH. YEAH.

13:40.515 --> 13:41.821
-BUY YOU A POT OF COFFEE?

13:41.951 --> 13:45.607
-[CHUCKLES] A CUP
WILL BE JUST FINE.

13:49.219 --> 13:51.526
-HIT THE WINCH AND
BRING IT UP. WE'RE DONE.

13:56.009 --> 13:58.054
HEY. WHAT'S WRONG?

13:58.185 --> 14:02.189
-HOSPITAL CALLED. NICK IS
GONNA NEED THAT OPERATION.

14:02.319 --> 14:04.147
-OH, POOR LITTLE GUY.

14:04.278 --> 14:05.583
-YEAH.

14:05.714 --> 14:06.802
-WHEN DO THEY NEED ME?

14:06.933 --> 14:08.760
-AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

14:09.892 --> 14:12.677
-[MAN GRUNTS]

14:16.116 --> 14:17.595
-IS THERE SOMETHING
I CAN HELP YOU WITH?

14:17.726 --> 14:19.554
-AS A MATTER OF FACT, THERE IS.

14:20.250 --> 14:22.426
YOU SEE, THERE'S SOMETHING
OF VALUE THAT I'VE LOST

14:22.557 --> 14:24.385
AND I WANT YOU TO FIND IT.

14:26.517 --> 14:27.475
-SORRY, I'M BOOKED.

14:27.605 --> 14:29.956
-[SCOFFS] NO, YOU'RE NOT.

14:31.131 --> 14:32.567
-I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

14:32.697 --> 14:35.439
-WELL, MAYBE THIS WILL
HELP YOU UNDERSTAND.

14:35.570 --> 14:38.442
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

14:42.794 --> 14:47.364
-MHMM. MHMM. YES.

14:48.017 --> 14:49.584
YES, I'LL DO WHATEVER I CAN.

14:50.672 --> 14:52.543
LET ME KNOW AS SOON
AS YOU HEAR FROM THEM.

14:53.457 --> 14:54.806
OKAY, THANKS.

14:58.767 --> 15:01.074
-HEY, KAYE! LOOK WHAT
THE CAT DRAGGED IN.

15:04.338 --> 15:05.774
WHAT'S WRONG?

15:06.340 --> 15:08.429
-NICKY'S DOCTOR JUST CALLED

15:08.559 --> 15:12.259
AND HIS BROTHER JAMIE'S SUPPOSED
TO BE THE BONE MARROW DONOR

15:12.389 --> 15:17.046
AND THEY CAN'T FIND
HIM, OR HIS WIFE.

15:17.177 --> 15:19.875
-THEY JUST DISAPPEARED?
JUST LIKE THAT?

15:20.006 --> 15:21.790
-IT LOOKS LIKE
HE WENT ON A DIVE,

15:22.878 --> 15:24.924
BUT NOBODY KNOWS FOR SURE.

15:26.360 --> 15:28.884
MITCH, IF NICKY DOESN'T
GET HIS TRANSPLANT,

15:29.972 --> 15:32.192
HE'S NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

15:43.246 --> 15:44.595
-THANKS.

15:45.945 --> 15:47.424
GARNER SAYS HE CAN'T DO ANYTHING

15:47.555 --> 15:49.470
UNTIL A MISSING PERSON'S
REPORT IS FILED.

15:49.600 --> 15:51.124
-THEN, IT'S ANOTHER 48 HOURS

15:51.254 --> 15:52.560
BEFORE THEY CAN GET
ON THE CASE, RIGHT?

15:52.690 --> 15:53.822
-YEAH.

15:53.953 --> 15:55.606
-NICKY DOESN'T HAVE THAT LONG

15:55.737 --> 15:57.217
AND IT'S TOO LATE TO
JOIN A DONOR'S CLUB.

15:58.174 --> 15:59.654
-HOW WELL DO YOU KNOW JAMIE?

15:59.784 --> 16:02.004
-I KNOW THAT HE WORKS
DOWN IN SAN PEDRO

16:02.135 --> 16:04.876
AND HE AND HIS WIFE OWN A
MARINE SALVAGING COMPANY.

16:05.007 --> 16:06.661
-WELL, YOU SPENT A LOT
OF TIME IN SAN PEDRO.

16:06.791 --> 16:08.793
YOU KNOW THE DOCKS LIKE
THE BACK OF YOUR HAND.

16:08.924 --> 16:10.317
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE CHECK IT OUT?

16:10.447 --> 16:12.319
-MITCH, I CAN BARELY
SEE THE BACK OF MY HAND.

16:13.059 --> 16:14.625
-YOU MAY NOT BE ABLE
TO HELP YOURSELF HERE,

16:14.756 --> 16:16.192
BUT MAYBE YOU CAN
HELP A LITTLE KID.

16:19.891 --> 16:21.589
-OKAY, I'LL DO IT.

16:21.719 --> 16:22.677
ON ONE CONDITION.

16:22.807 --> 16:23.895
-WHAT?

16:24.026 --> 16:25.158
-YOU LET ME DRIVE.

16:25.288 --> 16:27.290
-[LAUGHS] YEAH, RIGHT.

16:27.943 --> 16:29.640
DON'T WORRY. WE'LL FIND HIM.

16:29.771 --> 16:31.512
-THANKS. GOOD LUCK.

16:32.382 --> 16:33.993
-I CAN DRIVE, TRUST ME.

16:34.123 --> 16:36.082
-YEAH, LIKE I'M GONNA LET
YOU DRIVE MY CAR, RIGHT.

16:36.212 --> 16:37.561
-WHY NOT?

16:37.692 --> 16:38.823
-CAN'T EVEN SEE THE
BACK OF YOUR HAND.

16:38.954 --> 16:40.303
-SO? TELL ME WHEN TO TURN.

16:41.087 --> 16:42.523
-HELLO?

16:44.612 --> 16:45.787
ANYBODY HOME?

16:46.918 --> 16:49.356
-[SHIP HORN IN BACKGROUND]
-[DOG BARKING]

16:53.229 --> 16:54.796
-WHAT, ARE WE JUST
GONNA STAND HERE?

16:55.536 --> 16:56.885
-WHAT ARE YOU SUGGESTING?

16:57.016 --> 16:58.582
-I'M SUGGESTING WE
BREAK THAT PADLOCK.

16:58.713 --> 17:00.497
AFTER ALL, YOU WANNA SEE
WHAT'S INSIDE THERE, DON'T YA?

17:00.628 --> 17:02.499
-JUST HANG ON A
MINUTE, POWER RANGER.

17:02.630 --> 17:04.022
WHY DON'T WE GO AROUND BACK

17:04.153 --> 17:05.415
AND SEE IF THERE'S A
WINDOW SOMEBODY OPENED?

17:05.546 --> 17:06.851
-COME ON. THIS'LL
TAKE TWO SECONDS.

17:06.982 --> 17:08.896
HEY, GRAB THAT SPIKE THERE.

17:11.769 --> 17:13.554
-[GROANS LOUDLY]

17:13.684 --> 17:16.209
-ALL RIGHT. PUT IT RIGHT THERE.

17:17.775 --> 17:18.950
ALL RIGHT, HOLD IT STEADY.

17:19.080 --> 17:20.300
-WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT. [CHUCKLES]

17:20.430 --> 17:22.127
WAIT A MINUTE.

17:22.258 --> 17:23.867
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO'S LEGALLY
BLIND. YOU HOLD THE SPIKE.

17:23.999 --> 17:25.957
-THAT WOULD
PROBABLY WORK BETTER.

17:27.481 --> 17:30.179
-[METAL CLANGING]

17:30.310 --> 17:32.007
-YES. YES!

17:32.747 --> 17:34.792
-[CHAIN RATTLES]

17:38.013 --> 17:39.580
-GET IN.

17:42.757 --> 17:43.758
-WOW.

17:43.888 --> 17:44.802
-A LOT OF JUNK, HUH?

17:44.933 --> 17:45.803
-YEAH.

17:45.934 --> 17:47.066
-[METAL CLANGS]
-OW!

17:48.284 --> 17:50.808
HEY. CHECK THIS OUT.

17:51.679 --> 17:53.202
I SHOULD PROBABLY
GET ONE OF THESE

17:53.333 --> 17:54.638
TO KEEP FROM HURTIN' MY
HEAD EVERY TIME I BANG IT.

17:56.292 --> 17:57.859
-HERE'S A CALENDAR.

17:58.860 --> 18:01.254
AND NO WORK SCHEDULE 'TIL
THE END OF NEXT WEEK.

18:02.472 --> 18:03.952
WHAT ELSE WE GOT HERE?

18:04.648 --> 18:06.259
[CHUCKLES]

18:08.478 --> 18:09.610
-YOU KNOW, WE COULD
SPEND ALL DAY HERE

18:09.740 --> 18:10.698
AND NOT FIND ANYTHING TO GO ON.

18:10.828 --> 18:13.092
I HOPE YOU REALIZE THAT.

18:13.222 --> 18:16.225
-LOOKS LIKE THEY BUY MOST
OF THE THEIR EQUIPMENT
AT SOUTH BAY DIVING SUPPLY.

18:17.531 --> 18:18.662
THEY MIGHT KNOW SOMETHIN'.

18:18.793 --> 18:20.011
-LET'S CHECK IT OUT.

18:21.796 --> 18:24.103
-[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

18:26.148 --> 18:28.368
-YEAH. JAMIE SHOWED
UP HERE THIS MORNIN'.

18:28.498 --> 18:29.717
UH, BOUGHT A LIFT BAG.

18:30.500 --> 18:32.067
TWO GUYS WERE WITH HIM.

18:32.198 --> 18:33.938
KINDA LOOKIN' OVER HIS SHOULDER,
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

18:34.069 --> 18:35.244
-YOU KNOW THESE GUYS?

18:35.375 --> 18:36.811
-NO, I NEVER SEEN 'EM BEFORE.

18:36.941 --> 18:38.247
YOU KNOW, BUT COME
TO THINK OF IT,

18:38.378 --> 18:39.770
JAMIE SEEMED A LITTLE BIT JUMPY,

18:39.901 --> 18:41.816
LIKE HE'D HAD ONE
TOO MANY CAPPUCCINOS.

18:41.946 --> 18:43.296
THEY PAID IN CASH AND SPLIT.

18:44.035 --> 18:45.515
-DO YOU KNOW WHERE
THEY WERE DIVING?

18:45.646 --> 18:48.083
-UH UH. THEY DIDN'T SAY.

18:48.214 --> 18:49.476
GEES, I HOPE HE'S OKAY.

18:50.303 --> 18:51.652
-YEAH, SO DO WE.

18:52.218 --> 18:54.089
LOOK, IF YOU THINK OF
ANYTHING ELSE, HERE'S MY CARD.

18:54.220 --> 18:55.482
GIVE ME A CALL.

18:55.612 --> 18:58.789
-ALL RIGHT.
LIFEGUARD. [CHUCKLES]

18:59.312 --> 19:00.835
MUST BE A GREAT JOB.

19:01.575 --> 19:02.880
-MOST OF THE TIME.

19:04.360 --> 19:07.407
-[BEACHGOERS TALKING
INDISTINCTLY]

19:10.801 --> 19:12.368
-MATT: HI.
-HI.

19:13.369 --> 19:15.066
-THERE'S BEEN A RIP IN
THIS AREA ALL MORNING.

19:15.197 --> 19:16.677
I THOUGHT I'D LET YOU KNOW.

19:17.808 --> 19:19.332
-THANKS.

19:21.551 --> 19:22.900
-SO HOW'S CORT?

19:24.728 --> 19:27.078
-BETTER, I THINK.

19:28.384 --> 19:30.604
HELPING THAT LITTLE BOY HAS
GIVEN HIM SOMETHING POSITIVE

19:30.734 --> 19:31.953
TO FOCUS ON.

19:32.867 --> 19:33.998
-YOU'RE STILL IN LOVE
WITH HIM, AREN'T YOU?

19:35.217 --> 19:36.175
-NO.

19:37.524 --> 19:38.438
-DO ME A FAVOR.

19:40.004 --> 19:41.484
LOOK ME IN THE EYE
WHEN YOU SAY THAT.

19:43.007 --> 19:44.400
-WHY DON'T YOU BELIEVE ME?

19:47.273 --> 19:50.537
WHAT WOULD HAPPEN IF SUMMER
CAME BACK AND SHE WAS SICK?

19:53.017 --> 19:54.976
-I DON'T KNOW.

19:57.631 --> 19:59.023
LET ME THINK ABOUT IT.

20:03.811 --> 20:05.378
-[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

20:07.945 --> 20:09.991
-[BEACHGOERS TALKING
INDISTINCTLY]

20:12.863 --> 20:16.084
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

20:29.053 --> 20:33.623
♪ I'M SOMEWHERE IN THE MIDDLE
OF THIS HEARTBREAK ♪

20:34.755 --> 20:39.368
♪ YEAH FEELS LIKE AGES SINCE
THAT FIRE LIT MY HEART ♪

20:39.499 --> 20:43.851
♪ BUT BEFORE IT BURNED OUT IT LEFT
A TRACE OF GOLD ♪

20:44.591 --> 20:47.246
♪ TO SAY THAT YOU LOVE ME ♪

20:47.376 --> 20:51.380
♪ PUTS ME RIGHT BACK INTO AGONY

20:52.860 --> 20:58.866
♪ BUT YOU JUST NEVER WILL SEE

