-♪ YOU SAY THAT YOU LOVE ME

22:57.419 --> 23:01.380
♪ WOAH I'M FALLING APART

23:02.076 --> 23:05.035
♪ BECAUSE I CAN'T LET GO ♪

23:06.515 --> 23:10.824
♪ I'M SOMEWHERE IN THE MIDDLE
OF THIS HEARTBREAK ♪

23:16.090 --> 23:18.048
-[BEACHGOERS TALKING
INDISTINCTLY]

23:23.402 --> 23:26.013
-[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

23:27.318 --> 23:28.319
-EXCUSE ME.

23:28.450 --> 23:29.843
-YEAH?

23:29.973 --> 23:31.105
-WHY ARE YOU SWINGING
THAT BASEBALL BAT?

23:31.235 --> 23:32.889
-WELL, I'M A BASEBALL PLAYER.

23:33.020 --> 23:34.587
-BUT WHY DID YOU BRING
IT HERE TO THE BEACH?

23:34.717 --> 23:36.327
-WELL, I'M TRYING TO
KEEP MY SWING SHARP

23:36.458 --> 23:37.590
WHILE WE'RE ON STRIKE.

23:38.895 --> 23:41.245
-OH. JUST DON'T HIT ANYBODY.

23:41.985 --> 23:43.726
-HELP! OVER HERE!

23:43.857 --> 23:45.032
-EXCUSE ME.
-WOMAN: HELP!

23:45.162 --> 23:46.033
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

23:46.163 --> 23:48.209
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

23:49.210 --> 23:50.907
-GRAB THE CAN.

23:51.038 --> 23:53.040
I KNOW THE WATER'S SHALLOW,
BUT IT'S STILL DANGEROUS.

23:53.170 --> 23:54.955
YOU'RE IN A VERY
STRONG RIP CURRENT.

23:55.085 --> 23:56.435
-YEAH, IT IS STRONG!

23:56.565 --> 23:58.437
-[INDISTINCT TALKING]

23:58.959 --> 24:00.700
-NO MATTER HOW HARD I TRY,
IT KEEPS PULLING ME BACK.

24:00.830 --> 24:02.310
-I KNOW EXACTLY HOW YOU FEEL.

24:02.441 --> 24:05.835
-[WATER RUSHING]

24:06.575 --> 24:07.533
-THANKS.

24:07.663 --> 24:10.013
-YOU'RE WELCOME. YOU OKAY?

24:10.144 --> 24:11.537
-YEAH.

24:12.668 --> 24:15.366
HEY. AREN'T YOU MIKE PIAZZA?

24:15.497 --> 24:17.412
-YEAH. WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

24:18.195 --> 24:21.285
-[EQUIPMENT GROANING]

24:25.899 --> 24:27.509
-WATCH HIS FEET,
WATCH HIS FEET.

24:29.685 --> 24:31.339
-LET'S GET HIM
OUT OF THIS THING.

24:37.606 --> 24:38.825
-WELL?

24:38.955 --> 24:40.957
-[GASPING] I FOUND THE WRECK.

24:41.088 --> 24:43.482
-EXCELLENT. AND THE CARGO?

24:44.395 --> 24:46.136
-SCATTERED ALL
AROUND THE BOTTOM.

24:46.267 --> 24:47.964
YOUR CRATES BROKE OPEN.

24:48.095 --> 24:49.488
-FORTUNATELY,

24:49.618 --> 24:51.228
THE COCAINE IS WRAPPED
IN WATERPROOF PACKAGES.

24:51.838 --> 24:52.839
-LOOK, IT'S GONNA
TAKE ME A WHILE

24:52.969 --> 24:54.231
TO BRING ALL THAT STUFF UP.

24:54.884 --> 24:56.277
PLUS, IT'S GONNA BE DARK SOON.

24:56.407 --> 24:57.887
I CAN'T MAKE ANOTHER
DIVE UNTIL MORNING.

24:58.018 --> 25:00.368
-THAT'S NOT THE ONLY
PROBLEM. YOU HEAR THAT?

25:00.499 --> 25:02.065
-[MACHINERY PULSING]

25:02.196 --> 25:03.589
-YEAH, SO WHAT?

25:03.719 --> 25:05.504
-THE COMPRESSOR. IT'S
NOT RUNNING RIGHT.

25:05.634 --> 25:07.244
SOUNDS LIKE IT'S ABOUT
READY TO GIVE OUT.

25:07.375 --> 25:10.160
BETTER HAVE SOME AIR TANKS
READY TO GO, JUST IN CASE.

25:10.857 --> 25:13.512
-ALL RIGHT, IN THE
MORNING, WE'LL TAKE HER IN.

25:13.642 --> 25:16.602
BUT IF SHE'S FOLLOWED, YOU DIE.

25:20.083 --> 25:22.999
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

25:24.784 --> 25:28.439
-OH, HE CAUGHT IT. DOUBLE PLAY.

25:33.053 --> 25:34.054
-HEY.

25:34.837 --> 25:35.969
HOW'S HE DOIN'?

25:36.535 --> 25:40.408
-HE'S EXHAUSTED. DID
YOU HAVE ANY LUCK?

25:40.539 --> 25:41.844
-NOT ENOUGH.

25:43.019 --> 25:45.718
-MITCH, PEOPLE DON'T
JUST VANISH INTO THIN AIR.

25:45.848 --> 25:47.633
I MEAN, SOMETHING MUST
HAVE HAPPENED TO THEM.

25:48.198 --> 25:50.070
JAMIE WOULD NEVER DESERT
HIS LITTLE BROTHER.

25:50.200 --> 25:52.202
-KAYE, DON'T WORRY.
THE GUY WILL TURN UP.

25:53.508 --> 25:54.901
WE'LL GET THE WORD
OUT ON THE STREET.

25:55.031 --> 25:56.816
IF YOU WANT, I'LL
REARRANGE MY SCHEDULE

25:56.946 --> 25:58.818
SO WE CAN GO BACK TO THE
DOCKS TOMORROW MORNING.

25:59.993 --> 26:02.212
-MITCH, I'M SORRY I
JUST SNAPPED AT YOU.

26:02.778 --> 26:04.214
I MEAN, IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

26:04.824 --> 26:07.087
YOU'RE DOING MORE THAN
ANYBODY COULD EVER ASK.

26:08.131 --> 26:10.743
IT'S JUST THAT EVERY
TIME I LOOK AT NICKY,

26:11.439 --> 26:12.919
IT BREAKS MY HEART.

26:13.049 --> 26:14.485
-[VIDEO GAME
BEEPS IN BACKGROUND]

26:16.009 --> 26:18.751
-MATT IS CONVINCED THAT
I'M STILL IN LOVE WITH YOU.

26:20.709 --> 26:21.797
-ARE YOU?

26:23.277 --> 26:24.800
-I DIDN'T THINK SO.

26:25.627 --> 26:27.760
I'VE WORKED REALLY HARD
ON TRYING TO GET OVER YOU.

26:28.891 --> 26:30.545
EVERY TIME YOU ROLL
IN AND OUT OF MY LIFE,

26:30.676 --> 26:32.591
YOU LEAVE ME
WONDERING WHAT HIT ME.

26:33.809 --> 26:36.725
AND THEN, THE LAST
TIME THAT YOU LEFT,

26:38.335 --> 26:39.815
THAT'S WHEN MATT HAPPENED.

26:39.946 --> 26:41.600
-OH, I WAS SUCH A FOOL.

26:46.996 --> 26:50.260
YOU KNOW, C.J., I WAS
WONDERING IF UM...

26:52.611 --> 26:55.788
C.J.? C.J.?

26:58.181 --> 26:59.226
THERE YOU ARE.

26:59.356 --> 27:01.358
-I'M SORRY. WHAT
WERE YOU SAYING?

27:02.316 --> 27:04.623
-I WAS JUST THINKIN' THAT UM...

27:05.319 --> 27:06.537
-WHAT?

27:08.104 --> 27:11.151
JOHN. TALK TO ME.

27:13.327 --> 27:15.808
-LOOK, I KNOW I WAS
RUDE YESTERDAY AND...

27:17.723 --> 27:20.203
I JUST WANNA THANK YOU FOR
ALWAYS BEING THERE FOR ME.

27:23.642 --> 27:27.776
-HEY, CORT! THE DIVE
SHOP OWNER JUST CALLED.

27:27.907 --> 27:30.387
JAMIE'S THERE RIGHT NOW
WITH THOSE STRANGE TWO GUYS.

27:30.518 --> 27:31.998
LET'S MOVE!

27:33.216 --> 27:34.391
-I GOTTA GO.

27:37.481 --> 27:39.570
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

27:39.701 --> 27:42.661
-[BIRDS FLUTTER]
-[TIRES SCREECH]

27:47.404 --> 27:49.232
-HERE YOU GO,
GUYS. THAT'S THEM.

27:56.065 --> 27:58.372
-[PANTING]

28:02.071 --> 28:03.682
-I'LL TAKE CARE OF THIS.

28:04.552 --> 28:05.727
-[GROANS]

28:08.077 --> 28:09.426
-[GRUNTS]

28:10.645 --> 28:12.299
-[GRUNTS]

28:12.429 --> 28:14.214
-[GROANS]

28:16.216 --> 28:17.434
[GRUNTS]

28:20.481 --> 28:21.700
-[MITCH YELLS]

28:21.830 --> 28:22.701
-[GRUNTS]

28:23.876 --> 28:26.182
-[WATER SPLASHES]

28:26.313 --> 28:27.488
-[GRUNTS]

28:27.618 --> 28:29.446
-[WOMAN YELLS]
-[METAL CLANGS]

28:31.971 --> 28:33.537
-[BREATHING HEAVILY]

28:34.974 --> 28:36.236
-YOU'RE A THING OF BEAUTY.

28:36.366 --> 28:37.367
-WHO ARE YOU GUYS?

28:37.498 --> 28:38.978
-FRIENDS OF KAYE MORGAN.

28:39.108 --> 28:39.979
-YOU MUST BE ANNA.

28:40.806 --> 28:42.242
-WHERE'S JAMIE?

28:42.372 --> 28:44.026
-WE WERE KIDNAPPED BY
SOME DRUG SMUGGLERS.

28:44.157 --> 28:45.985
THEY FORCED HIM TO DIVE FOR
A LOST SHIPMENT OF COKE.

28:46.115 --> 28:47.682
-I'LL GET THE
COAST GUARD ON IT.

28:47.813 --> 28:49.510
-NO, YOU CAN'T.
THEY'LL KILL JAMIE.

28:49.640 --> 28:51.294
THESE GUYS ARE CRAZED.

28:51.425 --> 28:53.514
THEY SEE A COAST GUARD OR
ANYONE, THEY'LL KILL HIM.

28:54.254 --> 28:55.298
-[EXHALES SHARPLY]

28:56.473 --> 28:58.475
-[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

29:04.438 --> 29:05.569
-AREN'T YOU GONNA EAT ANYTHING?

29:06.614 --> 29:08.703
-CHEMOTHERAPY MAKES
ME SICK SOMETIMES.

29:11.793 --> 29:13.273
-I DON'T GET IT, MAN.

29:13.403 --> 29:15.841
I MEAN, IF IT'S SUPPOSED
TO MAKE YOU BETTER,

29:15.971 --> 29:17.581
WHY DOES IT MAKE
YOU FEEL SO BAD?

29:18.365 --> 29:20.367
-MY DOCTOR SAID IT'S
SORTA LIKE A LITTLE WAR

29:20.497 --> 29:21.934
GOING ON INSIDE ME.

29:23.762 --> 29:25.241
-YOU EVER GET SCARED?

29:25.372 --> 29:26.547
-SOMETIMES.

29:27.983 --> 29:29.811
-ARE YOU SCARED RIGHT NOW?

29:30.812 --> 29:32.161
-NOT REALLY.

29:32.945 --> 29:34.903
I HAVE A FEELING SOMETHING
GOOD'S GONNA HAPPEN.

29:35.599 --> 29:37.079
-WHO'S READY FOR DESSERT?

29:37.210 --> 29:38.472
-NO, THANKS.

29:38.602 --> 29:40.430
-NO? ARE YOU SURE?

29:41.431 --> 29:42.650
HOW ABOUT YOU, HOBIE?

29:42.781 --> 29:44.086
-UH, YEAH, I GUESS.

29:44.826 --> 29:46.219
-HAVE YOU HEARD
FROM MY BROTHER?

29:46.349 --> 29:50.353
-NO. NOT YET, BUT WE WILL.

29:50.484 --> 29:52.442
HOBIE'S FATHER'S LOOKIN'
FOR HIM RIGHT NOW.

29:53.226 --> 29:54.227
-[GLASS CLANGS]

29:54.357 --> 29:57.012
-[COUGHING AND GASPING]

29:57.143 --> 29:58.405
-NICKY, ARE YOU OKAY?

29:58.535 --> 29:59.406
-I'M SORRY.

29:59.536 --> 30:00.363
-NO, NO. THAT'S OKAY.

30:00.494 --> 30:01.887
-[COUGHS]

30:02.017 --> 30:03.802
-NICKY. NICKY, LOOK AT ME.

30:05.238 --> 30:07.066
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
CALL THE DOCTOR.

30:07.196 --> 30:08.850
NOW, WE MIGHT HAVE TO
GO TO THE HOSPITAL.

30:08.981 --> 30:10.678
-I'M OKAY. I'M FINE.

30:11.331 --> 30:12.680
PLEASE DON'T CALL.

30:12.811 --> 30:14.421
[COUGHS] EXCUSE ME.

30:14.551 --> 30:15.596
-WHERE ARE YOU GOIN'?

30:15.726 --> 30:16.684
-I NEED TO GO TO THE BATHROOM.

30:17.641 --> 30:19.252
[COUGHS]

30:22.124 --> 30:23.822
[COUGHS]

30:26.346 --> 30:28.827
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

30:34.180 --> 30:36.399
-[WATER BUBBLING]

30:41.883 --> 30:43.929
-[MACHINERY WHIRRING]

30:47.410 --> 30:48.759
-WHERE THE HELL ARE THEY?

30:51.458 --> 30:53.982
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

30:59.858 --> 31:02.034
-[WATER BUBBLING]

31:02.773 --> 31:04.471
-MATT: SO WHAT DO
YOU THINK I SHOULD DO?

31:04.601 --> 31:06.952
-FIRST OF ALL, YOU
NEED TO LIGHTEN UP.

31:07.082 --> 31:09.563
YOU'RE BLOWING THIS
WAY OUTTA PROPORTION.

31:10.346 --> 31:14.046
THE FACT IS, IF C.J.
REALLY LOVED CORT,

31:14.176 --> 31:16.396
THEN SHE WOULD'VE RAN
OFF WITH HIM BY NOW.

31:16.526 --> 31:18.441
-YEAH, BUT THIS
GUY NEVER GIVES UP.

31:19.007 --> 31:20.269
HE KNOWS SHE'S A SUCKER

31:20.400 --> 31:22.141
FOR HIS HELPLESS LITTLE BOY ACT.

31:22.793 --> 31:25.318
-SHE CAN SEE THROUGH ALL THAT.

31:25.448 --> 31:28.669
YOUR PROBLEM IS YOU JUST
DON'T GIVE HER ENOUGH CREDIT.

31:30.323 --> 31:31.628
-HAVE YOU GUYS SEEN NICK?

31:31.759 --> 31:32.891
HE NEVER CAME BACK
FROM THE BATHROOM.

31:33.021 --> 31:34.327
-WHAT?

31:34.457 --> 31:35.850
-YEAH, I DUNNO.

31:35.981 --> 31:37.634
I THINK HE JUST TOOK MY
BOOGIE BOARD AND SPLIT.

31:37.765 --> 31:39.506
-HE'S NOT STRONG ENOUGH TO
BE IN THE WATER BY HIMSELF!

31:39.636 --> 31:40.594
-I'LL CALL IT IN.

31:41.508 --> 31:44.163
-HOBIE, YOU KNOW THE BEACH
REAL WELL. PLEASE HELP ME.

31:44.293 --> 31:45.468
-ALL RIGHT.

31:47.166 --> 31:48.558
-HERE, WAIT. GRAB A BIKE.

31:48.689 --> 31:50.038
WE CAN GET A REALLY GOOD
VIEW FROM THE BIKE PATH.

31:57.611 --> 31:59.308
-[WATER RUSHING]

31:59.439 --> 32:01.310
-WOO HA!

32:06.968 --> 32:08.796
-[TIRES SCREECH]

32:13.409 --> 32:17.109
-I DON'T SEE HIM. HE
COULDN'T HAVE GONE THAT FAR.

32:17.239 --> 32:18.762
NOT IN HIS CONDITION.

32:18.893 --> 32:20.721
-COME ON. LET'S
JUST KEEP GOING.

32:25.334 --> 32:28.468
-[GROANING]

32:31.514 --> 32:33.952
-[APPREHENSIVE MUSIC]

32:36.693 --> 32:40.175
-[GROANS]

32:47.748 --> 32:50.969
-[WAVES CRASHING]

32:52.666 --> 32:54.798
-[MOANING]

32:59.281 --> 33:01.370
-OH MY GOD! THERE HE IS!

33:01.501 --> 33:04.373
GO, HOBIE! GO, HOBIE! GO!

33:04.504 --> 33:05.461
-NICK!

33:05.592 --> 33:06.941
-HERE WE COME! NICKY!

33:07.072 --> 33:09.074
-[BIRDS SQUAWKING]
-[WAVES CRASHING]

33:12.468 --> 33:14.079
-GOT HIM.

33:15.210 --> 33:17.082
-[INDISTINCT TALKING]

33:22.000 --> 33:23.740
-JUST LAY HIM DOWN RIGHT HERE.

33:25.960 --> 33:27.179
-HE'S UNCONSCIOUS!

33:28.267 --> 33:29.964
-TURN HIM OVER! TURN HIM OVER!

33:30.095 --> 33:31.574
-YOU'RE GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT, MAN.

33:31.705 --> 33:34.490
-OKAY, LAY HIM DOWN. HOLD
HIS HEAD. [STAMMERING]

33:38.799 --> 33:41.628
WE GOTTA GET HIM TO
THE HOSPITAL! NOW!

33:44.631 --> 33:46.589
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

33:49.592 --> 33:51.116
-ANNA: THAT'S OUR BOAT.

33:51.246 --> 33:52.943
-I THINK MAYBE YOU
SHOULD GET OUT THERE

33:53.074 --> 33:54.293
WHERE THEY CAN SEE YOU.

33:55.729 --> 33:57.992
-[GROANS]

33:59.733 --> 34:00.908
-YOU READY?

34:01.648 --> 34:03.258
-YEAH. SEEMS LIKE
OLD TIMES, DOESN'T IT?

34:04.216 --> 34:06.044
LET'S HOPE WE'RE NOT GETTIN'
OLDER, WE'RE GETTING BETTER;

34:06.174 --> 34:07.523
APPLIES TO EX NAVY SEALS.

34:07.654 --> 34:09.003
[CHUCKLES]
COME ON.

34:11.049 --> 34:13.964
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

34:22.842 --> 34:24.975
-[WATER SPLASHES]

34:27.456 --> 34:29.589
-[MACHINERY WHIRRING]

34:36.552 --> 34:37.553
-WHAT IS IT?

34:41.905 --> 34:43.210
-JUST A FISHERMAN.

34:44.299 --> 34:46.606
THEY SHOULDA BEEN BACK BY
NOW. SOMETHING'S NOT RIGHT.

34:49.870 --> 34:52.132
-[FISHING REEL CLICKING]

34:53.351 --> 34:55.789
-[WATER SPLASHING]

34:58.357 --> 35:00.576
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

35:05.625 --> 35:07.888
-[WATER BUBBLING]

35:12.414 --> 35:14.547
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

35:21.597 --> 35:23.730
-[MACHINERY WHIRRING]

35:27.734 --> 35:30.606
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

35:37.918 --> 35:41.313
[TENSION OF MUSIC INCREASES]

35:48.015 --> 35:50.060
-I DON'T LIKE THIS. SOMETHING
HAS HAPPENED TO THEM.

35:52.889 --> 35:54.152
LET'S GET OUTTA HERE!

35:55.153 --> 35:56.980
HERE, CUT OUR FRIEND LOOSE.

35:58.068 --> 36:00.506
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

36:03.335 --> 36:05.554
-[TENSION OF MUSIC INCREASES]

36:09.341 --> 36:12.344
-[WATER BUBBLING RAPIDLY]

36:18.828 --> 36:19.699
-HEY!

36:19.829 --> 36:21.353
-[GRUNTING]

36:22.789 --> 36:24.051
-AH!

36:29.012 --> 36:30.362
-[GROANING]

36:32.364 --> 36:34.975
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

36:36.237 --> 36:37.456
-[GRUNTING]

36:41.111 --> 36:42.939
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

36:43.810 --> 36:45.725
-[GASPS]

36:50.382 --> 36:52.166
-ARE YOU GUYS OKAY?
-[AIR HISSING]

36:52.297 --> 36:53.820
-THEY CUT JAMIE'S AIR HOSE.
-WHAT?

36:53.950 --> 36:55.648
-HOW DEEP IS HE?
-ABOUT 100 FEET.

36:55.778 --> 36:57.389
-HE'S GOT ABOUT A MINUTE AND
A HALF UNTIL HE SUFFOCATES.

36:57.519 --> 36:58.564
-ALL RIGHT. I'M
GOIN' AFTER HIM.

36:59.608 --> 37:01.001
JUST KEEP FEEDIN' ME SLACK, HUH.

37:01.131 --> 37:02.524
-CORT: GOOD LUCK.

37:02.655 --> 37:05.310
-[WATER SPLASHES]

37:09.401 --> 37:11.968
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

37:13.796 --> 37:15.755
-[WATER BUBBLING RAPIDLY]

37:18.148 --> 37:20.412
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

37:24.503 --> 37:26.853
-[WATER BUBBLING]

37:34.861 --> 37:36.602
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

37:38.604 --> 37:40.475
-[WATER BUBBLING RAPIDLY]

37:45.001 --> 37:46.612
-[PANTING]

37:49.571 --> 37:52.270
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

37:56.752 --> 37:58.188
-COME ON.

37:59.146 --> 38:01.061
-[WATER BUBBLING]

38:02.758 --> 38:04.804
-DO YOU SEE THEM?
-NOPE.

38:05.457 --> 38:08.242
-[WATER BUBBLING]

38:11.332 --> 38:13.160
-THERE. THERE THEY ARE.

38:13.856 --> 38:15.902
-[GASPING]

38:21.211 --> 38:23.605
-[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

38:30.873 --> 38:32.222
-PA ANNOUNCEMENT:
DOCTOR HAGAR TO OR.

38:32.353 --> 38:33.963
DOCTOR HAGAR TO OR.

38:34.964 --> 38:37.489
-[APPREHENSIVE MUSIC]

38:45.410 --> 38:46.759
-NICK: KAYE?

38:47.586 --> 38:49.370
-YES, SWEETHEART?

38:49.501 --> 38:51.372
-THANKS FOR TAKING
ME TO THE BEACH.

38:52.199 --> 38:53.505
I'LL NEVER FORGET IT.

38:53.635 --> 38:56.377
-OH, WE'LL GO AGAIN. OKAY?

38:56.508 --> 38:58.205
AS SOON AS YOU'RE BETTER.

39:00.076 --> 39:01.164
-[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

39:03.210 --> 39:05.343
-[MACHINES QUIETLY WHIRRING]

39:25.885 --> 39:27.321
-HEY, LITTLE BROTHER.

39:27.452 --> 39:29.279
-JAMIE.

39:30.498 --> 39:32.544
-[UPLIFTING MUSIC]

39:36.809 --> 39:38.158
-THANK YOU.

39:48.995 --> 39:50.692
-MITCH: OH, HEY.

39:50.823 --> 39:52.172
-HOW DID HIS SURGERY GO?
-[EVERYONE TALKING AT ONCE]

39:52.302 --> 39:53.652
-I CAN'T ANSWER ALL
YOUR QUESTIONS AT ONCE.

39:53.782 --> 39:55.654
THE SURGERY WENT
WITHOUT A HITCH.

39:55.784 --> 39:59.048
I SEE NO REASON WHY THE BONE
MARROW TRANSPLANT WON'T HOLD.

39:59.571 --> 40:02.878
NICHOLAS HAS AN EXCELLENT
CHANCE FOR FULL RECOVERY.

40:03.401 --> 40:04.532
-TERRIFIC!
-CORT: THAT'S GREAT!

40:04.663 --> 40:06.099
-ALL RIGHT!
-KAYE: THANK YOU.

40:06.229 --> 40:07.753
-FROM WHAT KAYE TELLS ME,

40:07.883 --> 40:09.842
YOU GENTLEMEN DESERVE
MUCH OF THE CREDIT

40:09.972 --> 40:11.670
FOR SAVING NICHOLAS'S LIFE.

40:11.800 --> 40:13.628
-YEAH. AND FOR
JAMIE AND MINE, TOO.

40:14.542 --> 40:16.152
-THANKS FOR BRINGING
ME ALONG, OLD BUDDY.

40:16.283 --> 40:17.545
-MY PLEASURE.

40:17.676 --> 40:19.025
-I HAVE A PATIENT
TO SEE. BYE BYE.

40:19.155 --> 40:20.374
-BYE BYE.
-ANNA: THANK YOU.

40:20.983 --> 40:23.725
-I PERSONALLY WANNA SAY THANK
YOU. THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

40:25.118 --> 40:26.685
-IT'S OKAY. [CHUCKLES]

40:26.815 --> 40:28.556
-HEY, [STAMMERS] WHAT ABOUT ME?

40:28.687 --> 40:29.862
[CLEARS THROAT] I WAS
A PART OF THIS, TOO.

40:29.992 --> 40:31.559
-YES. THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

40:31.690 --> 40:33.605
-RIGHT THERE, RIGHT
THERE. [MUMBLES] THANK YOU.

40:33.735 --> 40:34.693
-WHY DO YOU ALWAYS
GET THE SAME THING?
HUH, WHY DO YOU DO THAT?

40:34.823 --> 40:35.781
OH, I HAVE A PRESENT FOR YOU.

40:35.911 --> 40:37.043
-A PRESENT? YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE.

40:37.173 --> 40:38.131
-I DIDN'T.
-[CORT CHUCKLES]

40:38.261 --> 40:40.046
-IT'S FROM C.J. HERE IT IS.

40:40.176 --> 40:41.264
-OH, YOU'RE SO FUNNY.

40:41.395 --> 40:42.440
-[CHUCKLES]
-KAYE: UH OH.

40:42.570 --> 40:44.224
-PUT 'EM ON.
-OH, MITCH.

40:44.354 --> 40:45.443
COME ONE, YOU KNOW I CAN'T
SEE WITH THESE THINGS ON.

40:45.573 --> 40:47.053
-YOU CAN'T SEE WITHOUT 'EM.

40:47.183 --> 40:48.358
-DOES THIS MEAN
I CAN DRIVE NOW?

40:48.489 --> 40:49.490
-NO, YOU CAN'T DRIVE NOW.

40:49.621 --> 40:51.013
-WHY NOT?

40:52.362 --> 40:55.496
-SO JOHN D. CORT RIDES OFF
INTO THE SUNSET ONCE AGAIN.

40:56.889 --> 40:57.977
WHY DIDN'T YOU GO WITH HIM?

40:59.413 --> 41:00.719
-HE DIDN'T ASK ME.

41:01.894 --> 41:03.330
HE KNEW BETTER.

41:04.070 --> 41:06.028
HE UNDERSTOOD MY
FEELINGS FOR YOU.

41:08.727 --> 41:10.250
-I THOUGHT ABOUT WHAT YOU SAID.

41:11.686 --> 41:14.080
ABOUT IF SUMMER CAME
BACK AND SHE WAS SICK.

41:15.168 --> 41:16.386
AND YOU WERE RIGHT.

41:17.431 --> 41:19.259
I KNOW I'D HELP HER
ANY WAY I COULD.

41:20.565 --> 41:22.088
I'M GLAD YOU HELPED CORT.

41:23.742 --> 41:25.961
AND I'M GLAD THAT
SUMMER HASN'T COME BACK.

41:26.614 --> 41:27.702
-GOOD.

41:28.442 --> 41:30.662
-[BEACHGOERS TALKING
INDISTINCTLY]

41:36.015 --> 41:38.539
-[END THEME PLAYING]
